# Human wiki and staging (`wiki/`, `proposed/`)

- **LLM Wiki Manager (`wiki/`).** This checkout is **machine-first**. Optimize for **LLM comprehension and token efficiency** (tables, tight bullets, stable `##` anchors, no essay padding). **Human readability is out of scope** for **`wiki/`** prose style here. See **`schema/wiki-manager.md`** **Machine-first repository (LLM Wiki Manager)** and **`schema/human-wiki-automation-boundary.md`** **LLM Wiki Manager four-repo wiki**. **`schema/editorial-policy.md`** describes **human reader** norms for **domain child** repos. Do not mirror that voice in **Manager** **`wiki/`** unless a gate explicitly requires it.
- **Authorship boundary.** Final text stays explicit human or tasked-LLM work. Do not rely on scripts to merge or publish narrative silently. See **`schema/human-wiki-automation-boundary.md`**.
- **Evidence and parsers.** Follow **`schema/citation-spec.md`** and **`schema/wiki-quickstart.md`** where citations apply. **`scripts/validate_human_text.py`** over **`MD_GLOBS`** (**`schema/AGENTS.md`**) enforces **parse-safe** Markdown, not reader polish.
- **lint_wiki claim heuristic.** Long body lines starting with `- ` without **`[[sources/...]]`** become **info** rows in **`logs/lint/`**. **Operator** **`wiki/synthesis/`** pages (checkout maps, **`make`**, env) are usually not encyclopedic claims. Prefer **markdown tables** or **`##`** plus **bold** labels. **`karpathy-llm-wiki-bridge.md`** subsection **Operator synthesis and `lint_wiki.py` claim bullets**.
- **Root screenshots.** Optional **`llm_wiki_*.{png,jpg,jpeg}`** at repo root are **gitignored** by default (**README.md** Pre-push). **`SECURITY.md`** **Root screenshots** covers redaction before **`git add -f`** or public uploads.
- **Stop before handoff.** After substantive edits, run **`make wiki-check`** (Markdown-focused) or **`make wiki-ci`** (matches **`.github/workflows/ci.yml`** wiki leg). Optional stricter citation meta: export **`VALIDATE_WIKI_ARGS='--strict-citation-meta'`** before **`make wiki-validate`**, **`wiki-check`**, or **`wiki-ci`**. Full local parity with CI: **`make wiki-all`**.
- **Pytest and CI.** When **`make wiki-all`** or **`make wiki-test`** must match Actions and your shell **`pytest`** is stale versus **`requirements.txt`**, follow **README.md** (Pre-push and **Assistant preamble → repo mechanics** table), **`proposed/README.md`**, **`schema/wiki-quickstart.md`** (**Pytest and CI**), **`schema/karpathy-llm-wiki-bridge.md`** (**Pytest leg**), and **`schema/AGENTS.md`** (githooks bullet). Do not append extra **`make`** goals after **`make wiki-test`** (**`make wiki-test -q`** is invalid). **`prompts/wiki-edit.txt`**, **`prompts/wiki-corpus-authoring.txt`**, **`prompts/ingest.txt`**, **`scripts/githooks/README.md`**, **`Makefile`** (top comments), **`.github/workflows/ci.yml`**, **`.github/pull_request_template.md`**, **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/wiki-toolchain.md`**, **`tests/test_pipeline_step_order.py`**, **`tests/test_karpathy_bridge_docs.py`**, and **`tests/test_githooks_wiring.py`** repeat the same **`.venv`** + **`PATH`** recipe. Keep them aligned when the **`pytest`** pin in **`requirements.txt`** moves.
- **Suspected infra defects.** After **README.md** (Pre-push) checks, use **`schema/wiki-source-triage-protocol.md`** (Related) or **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/wiki-toolchain.md`**. **`.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml`** keeps blank GitHub issues when that checklist does not fit.
- **Fast inner loop.** **`make wiki-validate`** → **`make wiki-lint`** → **`make wiki-text`** as needed; they do not replace **`wiki-check`** / **`wiki-ci`**. See **`prompts/wiki-corpus-authoring.txt`** (iterative gate table).
- **Corpus / coverage work.** Load **`prompts/wiki-corpus-authoring.txt`** and **`schema/wiki-source-triage-protocol.md`**. Discovery: **`make wiki-topic-sources ARGS='…'`** (chains **`wiki-compile`**). Do not skip **`wiki-compile`** before graph-backed steps; do not mutate **`raw/`**.
- **Cold start.** Skim **`index/index.md`** and **`wiki/main.md`** before bulk page reads (**`schema/karpathy-llm-wiki-bridge.md`**).
- **Agent defaults in repo.** Root **`AGENTS.md`** points to schema and prompts. Prefer **`@prompts/wiki-edit.txt`** for small edits and **`@prompts/wiki-corpus-authoring.txt`** for exhaustive source passes instead of pasting long custom preambles.
- **Human automation without prose bots.** For "meticulously verify until satisfied," use **`make wiki-check`** / **`wiki-ci`** / **`wiki-all`** and optional **`scripts/githooks/`** (**`README.md`**, **Assistant preamble → repo mechanics**). Rollup signals only: **`make wiki-analyze`**.
